52#ifdef ACPI_OBSOLETE_FUNCTIONS
53#if defined(ACPI_DEBUG_OUTPUT) || defined(ACPI_DEBUGGER)
54
55#include "acnamesp.h"
56
57/*******************************************************************************
58 *
59 * FUNCTION: AcpiNsDumpOneDevice
60 *
61 * PARAMETERS: Handle - Node to be dumped
62 * Level - Nesting level of the handle
63 * Context - Passed into WalkNamespace
64 * ReturnValue - Not used
65 *
66 * RETURN: Status
67 *
68 * DESCRIPTION: Dump a single Node that represents a device
69 * This procedure is a UserFunction called by AcpiNsWalkNamespace.
70 *
71 ******************************************************************************/
72
73static ACPI_STATUS
74AcpiNsDumpOneDevice (
75 ACPI_HANDLE ObjHandle,
76 UINT32 Level,
77 void *Context,
78 void **ReturnValue)
79{
80 ACPI_BUFFER Buffer;
81 ACPI_DEVICE_INFO *Info;
82 ACPI_STATUS Status;
83 UINT32 i;
84
85
86 ACPI_FUNCTION_NAME (NsDumpOneDevice);
87
88
89 Status = AcpiNsDumpOneObject (ObjHandle, Level, Context, ReturnValue);
90
91 Buffer.Length = ACPI_ALLOCATE_LOCAL_BUFFER;
92 Status = AcpiGetObjectInfo (ObjHandle, &Buffer);
93 if (ACPI_SUCCESS (Status))
94 {
95 Info = Buffer.Pointer;
96 for (i = 0; i < Level; i++)
97 {
98 ACPI_DEBUG_PRINT_RAW ((ACPI_DB_TABLES, " "));
99 }
100
101 ACPI_DEBUG_PRINT_RAW ((ACPI_DB_TABLES,
102 " HID: %s, ADR: %8.8X%8.8X\n",
103 Info->HardwareId.Value, ACPI_FORMAT_UINT64 (Info->Address)));
104 ACPI_FREE (Info);
105 }
106
107 return (Status);
108}
109
110
111/*******************************************************************************
112 *
113 * FUNCTION: AcpiNsDumpRootDevices
114 *
115 * PARAMETERS: None
116 *
117 * RETURN: None
118 *
119 * DESCRIPTION: Dump all objects of type "device"
120 *
121 ******************************************************************************/
122
123void
124AcpiNsDumpRootDevices (
125 void)
126{
127 ACPI_HANDLE SysBusHandle;
128 ACPI_STATUS Status;
129
130
131 ACPI_FUNCTION_NAME (NsDumpRootDevices);
132
133
134 /* Only dump the table if tracing is enabled */
135
136 if (!(ACPI_LV_TABLES & AcpiDbgLevel))
137 {
138 return;
139 }
140
141 Status = AcpiGetHandle (NULL, METHOD_NAME__SB_, &SysBusHandle);
142 if (ACPI_FAILURE (Status))
143 {
144 return;
145 }
146
147 ACPI_DEBUG_PRINT ((ACPI_DB_TABLES,
148 "Display of all devices in the namespace:\n"));
149
150 Status = AcpiNsWalkNamespace (ACPI_TYPE_DEVICE, SysBusHandle,
151 ACPI_UINT32_MAX, ACPI_NS_WALK_NO_UNLOCK,
152 AcpiNsDumpOneDevice, NULL, NULL, NULL);
153}
